         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">March 11 /80 ¶ My dear Von Mueller ¶  ¶ The person to address on the subject of Miers' death ¶  is his son John Miers Jr. — an Engineer who had the construction of important works at Rio &amp; now lives i...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">80.03.11</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <ab rend="location"
                style="font-family: Geneva; text-align: center; font-size: 9pt; "
                type="heading">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</ab>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <ab rend="letter"
                style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
                type="heading">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS embossed with crest of Royal Gardens Kew. MS annotation by M: 'Answ 12/5/80 FvM'; see M to J. Hooker, 13 May 1880.</p>
               </note>March 11 /80</ab>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The person to address on the subject of Miers' death<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. Hooker, 31 December 1879 (in this edition as 79-12-31a).</p>
               </note> is his son John Miers Jr. — an Engineer who had the construction of important works at Rio &amp; now lives in England having still busness connections I believe with Brazil.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Many thanks for the nice collection of seeds just received. I am particularly glad of the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Grevillea%20annulifera">Grevillea annulifera</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg>.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>See M to J. Hooker, 8 January 1880.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We have had a very deplorable winter after a cold drenching summer. For two months we could do no garden work, &amp; now the weather has changed suddenly &amp; the buds are bursting just when I have an immense deal of transplanting to do.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>This winter finishes my arrangement of the Arboretum — &amp; I have just planted the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Castanea">Castanea</name>s</hi>
               </seg> &amp; <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Coryli</hi>
               </seg> in the places they will permanently occupy, &amp; am proceeding with <name key="Fagus">Fagus</name>, <name key="Ostrya">Ostrya</name>, &amp; <name key="Carpinus">Carpinus</name> as fast as I can. — It has been a twelve years job this planting the Arboretum. That formed by my father was all but ruined by the carelessness of the foreman of the ground, &amp; the fact that he was not allowed to cut down any trees or to buy good soil! The noble collection he brought together was consequently dislocated starved overgrown &amp; denuded of names.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I wish that more of your Australian plants would stand our climate, but you may count on your fingers all that will I put many against a sheltered South wall 2-3 years ago, but this winter has killed them all <name key="Eucalyptus%20polyanthemos">Eucalyptus polyanthemos</name> alone defies the winter, owing no doubt to its roots being deep in the Earth. E. <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">globulus</hi>
               </seg> has never stood 2 winters — one unnamed Tasmanian alpine one has dragged out a miserable existence for near 30 years but is a scare-crow.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever sincerely yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J D Hooker</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
